Installing the EventPubSub Example:

Step 1:
vi ~/Library/Application\ Support/BOXEE/UserData/profiles/<username>/shortcuts.xml
    <shortcut>
        <name>EventPubSub w/ Twilio</name>
        <path pathversion="1">app://eventpubsub/</path>
        <thumbnail pathversion="1">http://www.twilio.com/resources/images/homepage/logo.png</thumbnail>
        <private>false</private>
        <adult>false</adult>
        <country-allow>true</country-allow>
        <country>all</country>
    </shortcut>

Step 2:
Extract the contents of the zip into ~/Library/Application\ Support/BOXEE/UserData/apps/eventpubsub
cd ~/Library/Application\ Support/BOXEE/UserData/apps/
unzip ~/Downloads/eventpubsub.zip

Step 3:
Open Boxee and hit escape to see the shortcuts menu
You should then see a Twilio icon, click that.  You'll see a black screen when its started.
Now start playing a video.  You should now have messaging overlay during your playback.
